{{italic title}}
The '''''Encyclopedia of Reagents for Organic Synthesis''''' is published in print and online by [[John Wiley & Sons]] Ltd. The online version is also known as e-EROS. The encyclopedia contains a description of the use of all reagents in [[organic chemistry]]. The eight-volume print version includes 3500 alphabetically arranged articles and the online version is regularly updated to include new [[reagent]]s and [[catalyst]]s. 

