'''''Sarvavijnanakosam''''', known in English as the ''Malayalam Encyclopaedia'',<ref>{{cite book |title=Professor T.K. Venkataraman's 81st birthday commemoration volume |last=Venkataraman |first=T. K. |author2=S. Nagarajan |page=20 |year=1981 |publisher=Madurai Tamilology Publishers |oclc=9644941 }}</ref> is a general [[encyclopedia]] in the [[Malayalam|Malayalam language]]. It is intended to be "a compendium of world knowledge",<ref>[http://www.sarvavijnanakosam.gov.in/about-us.htm The State Institute of Encyclopaedic Publications]</ref> covering over 32,000 topics.<ref>{{cite journal |year=1972 |journal=Books India |publisher=[[National Book Trust]] |volume= |issue=2 |pages=72 |oclc= 1780786 }}</ref> The first volume was published in 1972,<ref name=Datta2006>{{cite book |title=The Encyclopaedia Of Indian Literature (Volume Two) (Devraj To Jyoti), Volume 2 |last=Datta |first=Amaresh |page=1167 |year=2006 |publisher=[[Sahitya Akademi]] |isbn=978-81-260-1194-0 }}</ref> and in 2015 sixteenth volume was published.<ref name="website">{{cite web |url=http://www.sarvavijnanakosam.gov.in/a-brief-his.htm |title=The State Institute of Encyclopaedic Publications: A brief history |publisher= Sarvavijnanakosam Website |access-date= March 4, 2017}}</ref> In total 20 volumes are expected to be published.<ref name="website" /> It is published by the [[State Institute of Encyclopaedic Publications]]. The encyclopedia received a national award for best reference book in 1979,<ref name=Datta2006/> and volume 12 received the [[Dravidian Linguists' Association]] award for best educational book of 2003.<ref>{{cite news |title=Award for encyclopaedia |url=http://www.hindu.com/2004/06/24/stories/2004062409710400.htm |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=24 June 2004 |accessdate=17 October 2010 }}</ref>
==Web edition== A web edition was launched in June 2008, which contains articles included in volumes 12, 13 and 15 of Sarvavijnanakosam as well as those in the revised editions of the first two volumes.<ref>http://www.sarvavijnanakosam.gov.in/about-us.htm</ref> The site uses a [[MediaWiki]] platform which allows the public to contribute.
